  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0db8\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd4 \u0dad\u0dd4\u0db1\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Three new committees for Parliament",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Speaker of the House Minister Susil Prema Jayanta informed the parliamentary party leaders today (24) that three more parliamentary standing committees are expected to be established based on the president's proposal.",
        "The leader of the House also stated that the sectoral monitoring committees to add amendments to the parliamentary standing orders will be set up promptly.",
        "The Committee on Parliamentary Affairs was held yesterday (24) morning at the Parliament complex under the chairmanship of Deputy Speaker Mr. Ajith Rajapakse.",
        "The President, as the Minister of Finance, has decided to present the opening speech (budget speech) of the second reading of the Appropriation (Amendment) Bill to Parliament on the 30th.",
        "Meanwhile, the adjournment debate on the electricity bill increase will be held on the 29th",
        "The Committee on Parliamentary Affairs also decided to hold the second reading debate on the Appropriation Bill on the 30th, 31st, 1st and 2nd of September.",
        "Also, three decrees under the Foreign Exchange Act, one resolution under the Customs Ordinance Act and two provisions under the Special Merchandise Tax Act are to be approved on the same day."
      ],
